On this computer, you may use the custom `table` CLI command to more easily
inspect the schema of the Rails application (which may be large).

Example:

```bash
$ table users
 create_table "users" do |t|
   t.string "name"
   t.string "email"
   t.string "password_digest"
   t.datetime "created_at", null: false
   t.datetime "updated_at", null: false
 end
```

Note that this will also include things like indexes, etc.
